WEBVTT

00:20.895 --> 00:22.105
Wind?

00:25.608 --> 00:26.818
You're up?

00:29.070 --> 00:31.698
I hailed a passing carriage.

00:31.781 --> 00:32.699
What?

00:33.575 --> 00:36.077
It must have been chilly up here
in just your bedclothes.

00:36.828 --> 00:38.329
We'll be arriving soon.

00:40.707 --> 00:42.917
See? There it is.

00:53.303 --> 00:54.846
My atelier.

00:55.346 --> 00:57.015
Your new place of study.

02:29.566 --> 02:32.986
EPISODE 2

02:33.069 --> 02:36.948
I've strewn guard briar seeds
around your house.

02:37.699 --> 02:41.452
They should grow quickly
to serve as a barrier.

02:41.953 --> 02:45.748
Since the house was turned to stone
by some unknown magic,

02:46.541 --> 02:49.460
I made sure no one would come too close.

02:55.675 --> 02:57.093
That's why...

02:58.511 --> 02:59.387
Coco?

03:04.642 --> 03:05.685
What's wrong?

03:06.811 --> 03:11.316
I promised my mom
I'd never leave her on her own,

03:11.399 --> 03:12.442
but I...

03:13.443 --> 03:14.527
Coco...

03:19.657 --> 03:21.075
Don't blame yourself.

03:21.576 --> 03:23.494
There was no way for you to know.

03:36.299 --> 03:38.343
Now, rinse your face.

03:39.010 --> 03:42.055
Let all the tears out, then look ahead.

03:44.724 --> 03:46.935
Starting today, this is your new home.

03:57.946 --> 04:00.156
Um, what's this?

04:00.240 --> 04:02.492
Hm? It's water.

04:05.578 --> 04:06.537
How could I forget!

04:06.621 --> 04:09.832
- I don't recall it being round and floaty.
- You need a change of clothes.

04:10.667 --> 04:11.584
Huh?

04:12.085 --> 04:14.587
How am I supposed to use this?

04:15.463 --> 04:16.798
Mr. Qifrey?

04:19.425 --> 04:22.845
I'm too scared
to touch magic I don't know.

04:22.929 --> 04:24.806
It's not scary!

04:25.473 --> 04:27.809
There's nothing tricky about that spell.

04:30.561 --> 04:32.855
Want me to show you?

04:36.526 --> 04:38.528
It's called a vapor bubble.

04:39.028 --> 04:42.448
It's a spell that draws moisture
from the air into water.

04:42.949 --> 04:44.284
Like this.

04:44.367 --> 04:45.451
Put your hands out.

04:46.786 --> 04:50.290
If you tip the lower tray,
it's like a spout.

04:50.790 --> 04:54.127
Wow, that's incredible! Thank you!

04:54.627 --> 04:56.587
- Thank you!
- Huh?

04:56.671 --> 04:59.924
I love it
when people say "thank you" to me!

05:00.008 --> 05:01.718
So, thank you!

05:01.801 --> 05:03.636
Oh.

05:03.720 --> 05:05.054
I see.

05:05.638 --> 05:06.806
Thanks.

05:06.889 --> 05:09.684
Thanks for your thanks!

05:09.767 --> 05:13.229
No, thank you for your thank-you
for your thank-you...

05:13.313 --> 05:15.606
If Tetia's being annoying, ignore her.

05:17.525 --> 05:19.861
She'll eventually stop
if you don't respond.

05:20.361 --> 05:22.572
How can you say that, Richeh?

05:22.655 --> 05:25.366
I was just teaching her.

05:27.702 --> 05:29.078
A pen and ink.

05:30.580 --> 05:32.665
Are you both witches?

05:32.749 --> 05:34.042
Apprentices.

05:34.542 --> 05:36.753
We're students of Master Qifrey.

05:36.836 --> 05:39.255
Wait, does that mean you're not?

05:39.964 --> 05:43.259
I assumed you're here to study
just like us.

05:43.343 --> 05:46.387
Are you the same age?
Which atelier are you from?

05:48.806 --> 05:51.392
I'm not really even an apprentice yet.

05:51.893 --> 05:55.688
I mean, I only drew
my first spell yesterday.

05:56.189 --> 05:58.274
I'll be living here starting today.

06:00.026 --> 06:01.110
- Huh?
- What?

06:02.362 --> 06:03.529
Um...

06:03.613 --> 06:06.783
Don't tell me... you're the one?

06:07.367 --> 06:09.035
I'm the one what?

06:17.085 --> 06:18.753
We heard a rumor

06:20.129 --> 06:23.132
that an outsider
who used a forbidden spell

06:23.633 --> 06:27.178
was allowed to become an apprentice
with memory intact.

06:29.263 --> 06:30.348
Coco.

06:32.308 --> 06:33.476
Are you okay?

06:33.559 --> 06:34.977
Mr. Qifrey.

06:35.561 --> 06:38.314
It seems you've already
introduced yourselves.

06:38.398 --> 06:41.234
Richeh, Tetia. When you're done
helping with morning chores,

06:41.317 --> 06:43.194
go study in your rooms.

06:43.277 --> 06:44.404
- Sure!
- Okay...

06:45.613 --> 06:46.781
Your change of clothes.

06:46.864 --> 06:48.574
Everyone wears these here.

06:51.160 --> 06:54.664
Don't be afraid. I'll explain everything.

06:57.291 --> 06:59.001
Fits you perfectly.

07:01.671 --> 07:04.966
Now, let's talk about magic.

07:06.092 --> 07:07.051
Yes.

07:08.511 --> 07:09.804
Long ago,

07:10.304 --> 07:12.723
magic was nothing special.

07:14.434 --> 07:18.980
All you needed were the right symbols
and special ink...

07:24.777 --> 07:26.821
and anyone could use it.

07:27.321 --> 07:29.407
It was far more accessible.

07:31.242 --> 07:32.994
But because of that,

07:33.077 --> 07:35.580
wars broke out again and again.

07:37.915 --> 07:41.919
When man has the power to do anything,
then anything he will do.

07:42.712 --> 07:45.548
Many horrifying spells were inscribed.

07:50.178 --> 07:52.597
The few good souls that remained

07:53.097 --> 07:56.517
renounced war
and banded together as witches.

07:57.018 --> 07:59.604
They erased the memory of magic
from the populace

07:59.687 --> 08:02.064
and passed on the knowledge
only to apprentices

08:02.148 --> 08:03.900
who could keep it secret.

08:05.109 --> 08:07.195
It was the "Day of the Pact."

08:08.112 --> 08:08.988
Since then,

08:09.071 --> 08:13.117
people have been led to believe
that only special people can wield magic.

08:13.659 --> 08:15.745
If the truth were to get out,

08:15.828 --> 08:18.331
we'd fall into chaos again in no time.

08:19.040 --> 08:22.418
Everyone is cautious to keep it hidden.

08:22.919 --> 08:24.837
That's why you were subject to rumors.

08:25.505 --> 08:26.422
I'm sorry.

08:26.923 --> 08:30.092
No, it's my own fault.

08:31.052 --> 08:34.096
Um, what is forbidden magic?

08:35.723 --> 08:40.436
Spells drawn during that age of war
and banned on the Day of the Pact.

08:41.312 --> 08:43.231
Magic that's meant to hurt people.

08:45.816 --> 08:47.902
Please teach me!

08:47.985 --> 08:49.862
All the spells we can't use!

08:49.946 --> 08:51.155
I want to know them!

08:52.865 --> 08:56.160
It's too frightening to go on not knowing.

08:58.913 --> 09:01.374
I'd tell you to be patient,

09:01.874 --> 09:03.668
but I can't in your case.

09:06.420 --> 09:07.463
Come with me.

09:12.552 --> 09:15.680
There are countless forbidden spells,

09:15.763 --> 09:18.641
but they can be summed up simply.

09:19.767 --> 09:23.980
Magic that directly affects the human body
or mind is always forbidden.

09:24.647 --> 09:27.483
For example,
transformation or changing age.

09:27.984 --> 09:30.945
Teleportation without doors or vehicles.

09:31.696 --> 09:33.948
Manipulating thoughts and emotions.

09:34.031 --> 09:36.325
Hurting or healing people.

09:37.326 --> 09:38.911
There is one exception though.

09:40.204 --> 09:42.081
The spell to erase memory.

09:42.164 --> 09:43.708
Exactly.

09:45.960 --> 09:48.296
Most spells are cast on tools.

09:50.172 --> 09:51.966
Like on carriages or lamps.

09:59.682 --> 10:02.518
Or windows like this.

10:22.204 --> 10:23.664
A lake?!

10:24.749 --> 10:27.501
It was all hills until a moment ago.

10:28.044 --> 10:29.503
It's a windowway.

10:30.004 --> 10:32.506
It connects to other windows
of the same design.

10:33.966 --> 10:35.718
See the building in the distance?

10:36.844 --> 10:38.054
The Tower of Tomes.

10:38.554 --> 10:40.181
To preserve knowledge,

10:40.264 --> 10:44.977
every book on magic
is copied here the moment it's written.

10:46.062 --> 10:47.563
That picture book too!

10:48.230 --> 10:51.067
Let's go right away!
I won't rest until I find it!

10:51.150 --> 10:51.984
Wait.

11:10.044 --> 11:11.671
That's the librarian's trial.

11:12.421 --> 11:15.549
The Tower of Tomes
is protected by four librarians.

11:15.633 --> 11:19.136
Only witches who have overcome the test
are permitted inside.

11:19.637 --> 11:22.890
To enter the tower,
you'll first have to study.

11:24.058 --> 11:24.892
Coco.

11:25.643 --> 11:27.687
I was happy earlier

11:28.187 --> 11:30.022
to hear you wanted to learn.

11:31.148 --> 11:33.025
It's natural to feel afraid.

11:33.609 --> 11:34.443
But...

11:36.320 --> 11:38.531
the spells that were not forbidden...

11:43.786 --> 11:46.831
are all means to bring people happiness.

11:48.124 --> 11:51.544
If you're going to learn,
I hope you learn more spells of kindness.

11:52.837 --> 11:53.879
Just a thought.

11:55.172 --> 11:56.090
What do you think?

11:57.425 --> 11:59.885
I'd like that, Master Qifrey!

12:03.973 --> 12:05.433
This is your room.

12:09.103 --> 12:10.938
Looks like Agott is out.

12:11.021 --> 12:12.356
Agott?

12:12.440 --> 12:14.191
Your roommate.

12:20.322 --> 12:22.575
Workspaces are two to a room.

12:23.075 --> 12:24.618
Bedrooms are private.

12:27.288 --> 12:31.041
Down the stairs in the back.
Don't worry, it has a lock.

12:32.209 --> 12:34.044
You should rest a little.

12:34.545 --> 12:37.673
I have some things to take care of,
but call if you need anything.

12:48.684 --> 12:50.644
This is Qifrey.

12:51.270 --> 12:54.732
Thank you for approving
Coco's apprenticeship.

12:56.066 --> 12:56.901
That's right.

12:58.110 --> 12:58.986
Yes.

12:59.528 --> 13:03.240
Not about the picture book yet.
She's still disoriented right now.

13:05.951 --> 13:08.829
So this is a witch's room.

13:10.539 --> 13:12.625
That's my desk.

13:24.345 --> 13:26.889
I'm coming down, so move.

13:27.932 --> 13:28.974
I'm sorry.

13:39.777 --> 13:41.362
You're Agott, right?

13:41.445 --> 13:42.988
- I'm Coco--
- I know.

13:43.739 --> 13:45.866
That outsider, right?

13:46.367 --> 13:49.119
I hear you're the new fellow apprentice.

13:50.412 --> 13:52.873
Such a shame about your mother.

13:54.625 --> 13:55.751
Thanks.

13:55.835 --> 13:57.711
Thanks to you...

14:00.256 --> 14:02.716
she'll never be human again.

14:04.426 --> 14:06.720
I came here to save her.

14:07.596 --> 14:08.722
To become a witch and...

14:11.517 --> 14:13.185
Ever since I was little,

14:13.269 --> 14:16.146
I've been drawing seals
until my fingers were stained with ink.

14:16.230 --> 14:18.274
I finally passed the exam
and became his student.

14:18.774 --> 14:21.277
Only then can you become an apprentice.

14:21.986 --> 14:24.280
You're ignorant and ordinary.

14:24.363 --> 14:27.533
An outsider like you could never cut it.

14:30.995 --> 14:34.081
I just tried and was able to do it.

14:34.665 --> 14:36.166
I won't know unless I try.

14:36.250 --> 14:38.377
Then prove it.

14:38.460 --> 14:40.546
- Take the test tomorrow.
- Agott!

14:40.629 --> 14:41.755
Coco!

14:41.839 --> 14:43.841
It's... time... to

14:44.341 --> 14:46.093
eat!

14:51.682 --> 14:53.601
I'm hungry.

14:53.684 --> 14:55.144
Me too!

14:55.227 --> 14:58.105
Today is Coco's welcoming party, right?!

14:58.188 --> 14:59.607
A feast...

15:07.781 --> 15:09.408
It's the same as usual.

15:10.409 --> 15:12.745
Master! What about the party?

15:13.329 --> 15:16.749
It was short notice.
We'll celebrate another time.

15:17.249 --> 15:18.375
Where's Agott?

15:18.459 --> 15:20.252
She said she'd eat in her room.

15:20.961 --> 15:24.214
It'd be nice if we could
all eat together for once.

15:24.757 --> 15:26.842
Okay, let's eat.

15:27.343 --> 15:30.346
Let's have Coco do the honors.

15:30.429 --> 15:32.181
Huh? Oh, okay!

15:33.474 --> 15:34.600
Let us eat.

15:35.142 --> 15:36.518
- Let's eat.
- Let's eat.

15:44.151 --> 15:45.277
It's delicious.

15:45.361 --> 15:48.656
Isn't it? It's baked here.

15:49.156 --> 15:50.866
The master is a master chef.

15:50.950 --> 15:51.909
Amazing.

15:52.701 --> 15:54.912
The local grain is really good.

16:03.837 --> 16:06.757
The local vegetables are delicious.

16:07.341 --> 16:09.343
Thank you for the meal.

16:34.493 --> 16:35.661
Mom.

16:45.504 --> 16:49.341
A test is required
to become an apprentice.

16:50.342 --> 16:55.180
But it doesn't really say
what you have to do.

16:55.681 --> 16:57.141
What doesn't it say?

16:59.518 --> 17:02.896
There's a lot about magic
that isn't written in books.

17:02.980 --> 17:05.899
To learn it, you have to experience it.

17:06.900 --> 17:07.943
What's this?

17:08.527 --> 17:09.945
Your materials.

17:10.029 --> 17:11.697
Your tools for casting.

17:14.783 --> 17:17.661
They're so cool!

17:19.788 --> 17:22.416
The magic wand... pen.

17:23.542 --> 17:25.627
I'm still a little scared.

17:25.711 --> 17:26.587
But...

17:27.463 --> 17:30.424
Mom, I'm gonna get you back to normal.

17:31.425 --> 17:33.844
I'm ready, Master Qifrey.

17:34.428 --> 17:36.055
Alright then, let's begin.

17:43.353 --> 17:44.396
Are you okay, Coco?

17:44.897 --> 17:46.231
Shall we take a break?

17:47.149 --> 17:49.193
No, I'm okay.

17:50.819 --> 17:53.947
Then repeat back to me
what you understood.

17:54.031 --> 17:55.657
Oh, okay.

17:56.283 --> 17:57.409
Well...

17:57.493 --> 18:00.454
Spells are composed of three elements.

18:01.789 --> 18:03.373
A "sigil" in the center,

18:03.999 --> 18:07.127
surrounded by lines called "signs,"

18:07.628 --> 18:10.964
and the "ring" that completes that seal.

18:11.048 --> 18:13.342
Sigils are different for fire,

18:14.676 --> 18:15.552
water,

18:16.386 --> 18:17.304
light,

18:18.555 --> 18:19.556
and wind...

18:19.640 --> 18:22.601
And that determines the type of spell.

18:23.310 --> 18:26.396
The signs determine what form
the spells will take

18:26.480 --> 18:28.941
as well as their size and direction.

18:29.942 --> 18:32.945
And by completing the outer ring,

18:33.028 --> 18:36.240
the seal is closed,
and the spell activates.

18:37.449 --> 18:40.953
I'm at my limit just memorizing it.

18:41.036 --> 18:42.621
But you did it!

18:45.124 --> 18:46.917
I'm gonna give it a try.

18:47.000 --> 18:49.002
Wonderful. That's the spirit!

19:05.227 --> 19:07.146
No, don't throw it away!

19:08.397 --> 19:09.898
No!

19:09.982 --> 19:12.401
I can't show you this!

19:12.484 --> 19:16.405
It's terrible, and the lines
are all shaky and wobbly.

19:16.989 --> 19:19.700
Of course. You've only just started.

19:20.242 --> 19:22.870
More importantly, you need to look here.

19:23.871 --> 19:26.665
See? The ring is broken.

19:26.748 --> 19:29.793
If it isn't connected,
the spell won't activate.

19:33.255 --> 19:36.425
Hands tend to be unsteady
when using a new tool.

19:36.925 --> 19:39.553
Like a newborn foal trying to stand.

19:40.137 --> 19:43.557
You'll get used to it soon
and be running around in no time.

19:45.392 --> 19:48.896
Now, close the seal and try activating it.

20:03.744 --> 20:06.163
I'm so sorry! It wasn't on purpose!

20:09.249 --> 20:12.252
I'm sorry! I'll dry it! Let me dry it!

20:13.587 --> 20:15.422
- Calm down, Coco.
- Did it dry?

20:15.505 --> 20:16.590
I'm sorry, Agott.

20:16.673 --> 20:17.925
- Are you all right?
- Not yet?

20:19.593 --> 20:21.428
It's fine, Master.

20:21.929 --> 20:23.805
It doesn't bother me.

20:24.389 --> 20:27.517
But can I see Coco's seal, please?

20:27.601 --> 20:29.311
Huh? Sure.

20:31.355 --> 20:32.564
Here it is.

20:37.194 --> 20:38.153
Look.

20:39.238 --> 20:41.281
This one sign is longer.

20:41.782 --> 20:46.328
It's applying too much pressure
and causing the water to spurt.

20:46.912 --> 20:49.998
As always,
your observations are spot on, Agott.

20:51.250 --> 20:54.586
Yes, I think I can leave it to you.

20:54.670 --> 20:55.545
What?

21:00.884 --> 21:02.678
I'll be away for the next few days.

21:02.761 --> 21:04.805
I'm going to the witch's Great Hall.

21:05.305 --> 21:08.558
Agott, please look after Coco
while I'm gone.

21:09.142 --> 21:10.894
Yes, Master.

21:12.145 --> 21:13.563
Wait, please.

21:13.647 --> 21:15.899
There's much you can learn
from your peers.

21:15.983 --> 21:18.777
Watch and learn from her, Coco.

21:20.195 --> 21:22.531
Master...

21:26.410 --> 21:29.538
Um, I'm really sorry. I--

21:29.621 --> 21:31.540
Stop apologizing.

21:31.623 --> 21:33.333
I said it doesn't bother me.

21:34.626 --> 21:36.211
Now, Coco.

21:37.713 --> 21:41.216
I asked you to prove yourself yesterday.

21:41.717 --> 21:44.636
It's time to get serious.

21:45.345 --> 21:47.222
Your test starts now.

21:48.307 --> 21:49.266
What?

23:30.909 --> 23:34.996
Subtitle translation by: Emily Noguchi

23:36.706 --> 23:40.502
EPISODE 3
